Mathéo Galuba is a skilled and innovative computer science student based in France, with a strong foundation in programming languages such as C++, C, and Swift. With a growing professional network of over 38 followers, he has established himself as a knowledgeable and reliable developer in the open-source community. His impressive portfolio of 29 public repositories showcases his active involvement in various development projects, demonstrating his technical expertise and passion for creating high-quality software solutions.

As a dedicated maker and open-source enthusiast, Mathéo brings a unique combination of creativity and technical skills to the table. With a solid understanding of computer science principles and a keen interest in staying up-to-date with the latest industry trends, he is well-equipped to tackle complex development challenges and deliver innovative solutions. With his strong work ethic and commitment to excellence, Mathéo has positioned himself as a talented and promising young developer in the field, with a bright future ahead in the world of software development and open-source technology.
